## §1 Auth / role enforcement

**Detected pattern**: {{AUTH_PATTERN}}

<!-- One of:
- @nestjs/passport + JWT strategy + @UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard) + custom RolesGuard
- Keycloak adapter (e.g., nest-keycloak-connect)
- Custom guard reading Authorization header
- Clerk / Auth0 adapter
- Delegated to API gateway (no in-service auth)
- No auth (internal / worker service)
-->

**Rules:**
- {{AUTH_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Protected routes use `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard)` + `@Roles('ADMIN')` — declarative, at the controller or handler level.
- Do NOT read the request.user object directly from `@Req()` to check roles; use the RolesGuard.
- Public routes are explicitly marked with `@Public()` (metadata reflector pattern) — no accidental exposure.
-->

