## §5 Module layout & DI

**Module structure**: {{MODULE_PATTERN}}

<!-- e.g.:
- One feature module per domain concern (UsersModule, BooksModule, ...)
- Each module owns its controllers, services, providers, DTOs
- Cross-module dependencies via exported providers (no circular imports — use forwardRef only when unavoidable)
-->

**DI style**: {{DI_PATTERN}}

<!-- Almost always: constructor injection. Call out if there's any property injection. -->

**Controller style**: {{CONTROLLER_PATTERN}}

<!-- e.g.:
- Controllers implement OpenAPI-generated interfaces (via nestjs-openapi-gen / nest-openapi-tools)
- Or: hand-decorated @Controller + @Get/@Post + @ApiOperation (for Swagger)
- Global ValidationPipe enabled in main.ts — DTOs use class-validator decorators
-->

**Rules:**
- {{MODULE_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Every provider (service, repository, factory) is registered in its module's `providers:` array.
- Exports only what other modules need — keep the surface minimal.
- `forwardRef()` is a smell — if you find yourself reaching for it, consider restructuring.
-->

**Reference files:**
{{MODULE_REFERENCES}}

