## §6 Error handling

**Global filter**: {{ERROR_FILTER}}

<!-- e.g.:
- A global @Catch() ExceptionFilter registered in main.ts, mapping custom exceptions to {statusCode, code, message}
- NestJS built-in HttpException + exception filter extended for consistent error envelopes
- Middleware-based error handling (rare; flag if seen)
-->

**Exception hierarchy**: {{EXCEPTION_HIERARCHY}}

<!-- Custom exceptions extend a domain base (e.g., DomainException) or HttpException -->

**Rules:**
- {{ERROR_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Services throw specific exception types (UserNotFoundException, InvalidCredentialsException).
- Never throw raw `Error` or generic `BadRequestException` from services — lose the error code specificity.
- New exception classes live in `src/{feature}/exceptions/` and are mapped in the global filter (or extend a base that carries the error code).
-->

**Reference files:**
{{ERROR_REFERENCES}}

