## §7 Tests

**Unit test harness**: {{UNIT_TEST_PATTERN}}

<!-- Jest via @nestjs/testing Test.createTestingModule() — mock providers with .overrideProvider().useValue() -->

**Integration / e2e test harness**: {{E2E_TEST_PATTERN}}

<!-- supertest against app.getHttpServer(), with a dedicated AppModule (or TestAppModule) that wires in-memory / testcontainers DB -->

**Security test pattern** (if auth is enforced): {{SECURITY_TEST_PATTERN}}

<!-- e.g.:
- e2e tests with mocked JwtAuthGuard + custom user contexts per test
- Passport strategy override at test-module level
- "Not established yet — first feature to add role gates establishes it"
-->

**Rules:**
- {{TEST_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Every new controller endpoint has a unit test (service method) + an e2e test (HTTP roundtrip).
- When a guard is added / modified, a security e2e test is mandatory: covers allowed roles, denied roles, no-auth → 401.
- Mock data in tests matches the real wire shape — no "simplified" shortcuts.
-->

**Reference files:**
{{TEST_REFERENCES}}

